metadata.name: ・X・
metadata.description:
Since ancient times, the Japanese have personified the twelve signs of the Chinese zodiac, which govern the year, to wish for prosperity during the year.
This year is the Year of the Rabbit, so I drew a beautiful Japanese bunny girl.
In my opinion, I believe that loincloths, the Japanese underwear, evoke a certain excitement.

As a side note, I came up with the above common belief while drinking whisky earlier in the day.

Translated with www.DeepL.com/Translator (free version)
